<p>A closure is <strong><em>a function within a function</em></strong> that has access to its "parent" function's variables and parameters.</p>

<p>Example:</p>

<pre><code>function showPostCard(Sender, Receiver) {

    var PostCardMessage = " Happy Spring!!! Love, ";

    function PreparePostCard() {
        return "Dear " + Receiver + PostCardMessage + Sender;
    }

    return PreparePostCard();
}
showPostCard("Granny", "Olivia");
</code></pre>
